criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with LARS score ≥ 21 after anterior resection of the rectum with
             sphincter-saving surgery for rectal cancer;

          -  Age> 18 years;

          -  Obtaining informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients carrying ostomy;

          -  Patients with clinical or radiological evidence of local or distant tumor recurrence;

          -  Patients suffering from neurological disorders;

          -  Patients with Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD);

          -  Patients who have a pacemaker or defibrillator;

          -  Patients taking antiplatelet agents or anticoagulants;

          -  Patients unable to follow the procedures of the Protocol or to provide informed
             consent.
